body:
@original-brownbear The two timestamps are generated by different threads and the one generated by the `Sender` thread is generated at the start of the iteration. Given that, it's very much possible for the batch to have been created after the `Sender` thread iteration started. I made a few complementary improvements to the ones done in your PR here:

https://github.com/ijuma/kafka/commit/069df8d576ecd9e534140a8c6b3503424e162307

Would you like to integrate them into your branch?

@enothereska wrote:
> This led to most of the efficiency increases in streams consumption vs. simple consumer. Streams performance went from ~60MB/s -> 97MB/s (request size is 100 bytes).

Hey, great job!
